次第　顺序/情况 
次第 (shidai) is a noun that means "circumstances" or "situation"
--天気次第で外出する予定です。(Tenki shidai de gasshutsu suru yotei desu.)"I plan to go out depending on the weather."
--予算次第で旅行の行き先が決まります。(Yosan shidai de ryokō no ikisaki ga kimarimasu.)"The travel destination will be decided depending on the budget."

It is often used with the particle で (de) to mean "depending on"
--状況次第で対応が変わります。(Jōkyō shidai de taiō ga kawarimaasu.)"The response will change depending on the situation."
--成績次第で進路が決まります。(Seiseki shidai de shinro ga kimarimasu.)"The career path will be decided depending on the grades."

It can also be used with the particle に (ni) to mean "according to"
--規則次第に行動しなければなりません。(Kisoku shidai ni kōdō shinakereba narimasen.)"You must act according to the rules."
--計画次第に進めていきます。(Keikaku shidai ni susumete ikimasu.)"We will proceed according to the plan."

次第 is often combined with other words to form set phrases
状況次第 (jōkyō shidai) - "depending on the situation"
時間次第 (jikan shidai) - "depending on the time"
用事次第 (yōji shidai) - "depending on the errand/task"
　
